senses.sense: The 24<sup>th</sup> letter of the English alphabet, called ex and written in the Latin script.
Forming gender-neutral or otherwise more inclusive versions of words, especially Spanish-derived words by replacing both the masculine -o and feminine -a.
examples: alumnx, Chicanx (Xicanx), Filipinx, Latinx, Mx, mxn, Tejanx, womxn

senses.sense: Alternative letter-case form of X ("intersex or non-binary, in passports and identification documents")
(sometimes humorous) An unknown or unspecified number of.
(fandom) Used between the names of two characters to denote a ship, particularly in anime, manga, and video games.
(music) Used in place of and in artist collaborations.
examples: Taska Black x DROELOE, Steve Aoki x Lauren Jauregui, etc.
